<title type="html"><![CDATA[Win 10 Creator home screen blinks -forced uninstall of 4.3.0]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7724&amp;p=33208#p33208"><![CDATA[
After update to W10 Creator, the home screen would 'refresh' (rebuild) every ~3 seconds.  Nearly impossible to use the PC as any command (or click) needed to be completed within this time (~3 secs).<br />CTRL-ALT-DEL about all that was do-able, and even then STOPPING a process (ClassicShell) was difficult.<br />Finally stopped and Problem stopped.<br /><br />Uninstalled 4.3.0, rebooted and no problem.<br />Re-DL'ed,  installed 4.3.0 and reboot and problem returned.<br /><br />Uninstalled.<br /><br />Been using CS since Win8, love it and hope you can fix.<br />thx<br /><br /><span style="color:#333333;"><span style="font-family:Arial, sans-serif;">HP</span></span><span style="background-color:#d82300;"><span style="color:#ffffff;"><span style="font-family:Arial, sans-serif;">ENVY</span></span></span><span style="color:#333333;"><span style="font-family:Arial, sans-serif;">TOUCHSMART 15-J150US</span></span><br /><span style="color:#333333;"><span style="font-family:Arial, sans-serif;">Win 10 Pro - 15063.413</span></span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21530">songwoods</a> — Fri Jul 07, 2017 4:51 am</p><hr />
